      <description>&lt;p&gt;The &lt;strong&gt;WIP limit&lt;/strong&gt; (work-in-progress limit) is the concurrency bound&#xA;on closure: at most 2-3 plans in the Active column of the&#xA;&lt;a href=&#34;./board.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;board&lt;/a&gt; at any time.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This is not arbitrary. Too many simultaneous partial closures means&#xA;none complete. Energy disperses. The system thrashes without making&#xA;progress toward any single &lt;a href=&#34;./closure-condition.md&#34; class=&#34;link-internal&#34;&gt;closure condition&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;The WIP limit comes from Kanban practice (Anderson, 2004) and is&#xA;reinterpreted here as a constraint on how many closure processes&#xA;the system can sustain concurrently.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
